.TH "fm10k_update_lport_state_pf" 9 "fm10k_update_lport_state_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_update_lport_state_pf \- Notify the switch of a change in port state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_update_lport_state_pf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 glort "  ","
.BI "u16 count "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "glort" 12
base resource tag for this request
.IP "count" 12
number of logical ports being updated
.IP "enable" 12
boolean value indicating enable or disable

This function is used to add/remove a logical port from the switch.
